**Reference:**  
Yang Luo, Jing Wang, Yan Xiao, Wen-Jun Li, Shi-Ying Wang, Zi-Yi Ding, Yan-Hong Liu, Hong-Yu Zhang, Ben-Xun Su. (2023).  
Natural ilmenite reference material for trace elemental in situ microanalysis.  
<i>Spectrochimica Acta Part B: Atomic Spectroscopy</i>, 209, 106798.  

[View article at Elsevier](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.sab.2023.106798)

Ilmenite is a common mineral in igneous and metamorphic rocks used as a geothermometer, oxygen barometer, and geochemical tracer. This study developed a 500 g ilmenite megacryst (sample LY) as a reference material for in situ elemental microanalysis. Twenty-two ilmenite fragments (1-8 mm grain size) were analyzed using EMPA and LA-ICP-MS across four laboratories.

The sample shows homogeneity for TiOâ‚‚, FeO, Mg, Sc, V, Cr, and Mn, with minor inhomogeneity observed in Co and Nb. These results indicate the sample's suitability as a reliable reference material for major and trace element in situ microanalysis.
